 have been through with their child, what they were told by professionals and what their situation is - I think that is an extremelly unfair judgement. &#10;I am about the last &quot;let's make things easy&quot; for our kids person I know. Friends and family actually think we are too hard on our kids. We are pretty &quot;old school&quot; parents. We don't take the easy way out on anything. I don't do any of that helicopter parenting crap that other people do either. &#10;So to say that I am holding my son back because it is &quot;easy&quot; is offensive to me. You don't know our situation or my child. Please try to refrain from making snap judgments to all people in this situation. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="946" language="en" documentId="5090" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="mummyto2cuties" date="04/03/2012" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://community.babycenter.com/post/a32503567/yet_another_redshirting_debate?cpg=3" topic="redshirting" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="5090" notes="" title="Yet another redshirting debate"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="97"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="98" end="445"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="446" end="740"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="741" end="946"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>